-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Compile the Code
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

To compile the code run the make command in the top directory:

    make

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Run word count programme
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

To run the word count programme, the path to the text file, relative to the top directory, 
must be specified. For example, to run the word count programme with the Dracula.txt:

./wordCount/wordCount Dracula.txt

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Run top k programme
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

The top k programme requires the path to the text file, relative to the top directory, 
and the number of words to print. To run the top k programme for Dracula.txt and print 50 words:

./top50/top50 Dracula.txt 50

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Run inverted index programme
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The inverted index programme requires the path to the text file, relative to the top directory.
To run the inverted index programme with the Dracula.txt:

./invert/invertedtext Dracula.txt